<span class="displaytext"><b>woodbridge, n.j.--</b> u.s. senator (candidate full)'s presidential campaign today announced that mayor richard j. gerbounka (linden, n.j.) has endorsed (candidate full) for president. <p>"i am proud to support (candidate full) for president," said mayor gerbounka. "(candidate full) is a bipartisan reformer with the judgment and experience necessary to lead on the tough issues that matter most to linden residents." </p><p>mayor gerbounka formally endorsed (candidate full) in a press conference held today on the steps of linden city hall. state senator bill baroni, who serves as the new jersey chairman for (candidate full)'s presidential campaign, was on hand to welcome the endorsement. </p><p>"we are pleased to have mayor gerbounka on board and his endorsement speaks to (candidate full)'s leadership and broad appeal in new jersey. the mayor's support will help swing this heavily-(PARTY NAME) area for (candidate full)," senator baroni said. "(candidate full) has always and will always put his country's interests before any party, any special interest and even his own self-interest. the residents of linden will always know exactly where (candidate full) stands." </p><p>mayor gerbounka, a lifelong (PARTY NAME) who ran as an independent in 2006, represents a city that is strategically important for senator (candidate last)'s plan to win new jersey. </p><p>tomorrow, mayor gerbounka and senator baroni will greet senator (candidate last) when he arrives in new jersey. this will be the senator's sixth campaign stop in the garden state since declaring his candidacy. </p><p>along with mayor gerbounka, linden city council members bruce howe, joe harvanik, jack sheehy and bob frazier also endorsed (candidate full) today. howe, harvanik and frazier are independents; sheehy is a (PARTY NAME).</p></span>



